{
  "text": "Once cells were trapped, the entire self-assembly setup was submerged upright in medium and cells were left to attach overnight at 37 \u00b0C in a 5% CO 2 incubator. The ceiling used during self-assembly was then removed. The cells were next stained with the same dyes previously described to verify vitality and sealed using inverted microwells containing sensor that aligned over each cell micro-trap ( Figure 3 ). The glass ceiling was fabricated by a chrome lift-off step using conventional photolithography followed by etching microwells into the glass using hydrofluoric acid. The chrome was then removed to result in a 3-by-3 array of 115 \u00b5m diameter and 45 \u00b5m deep wells spaced 300 \u00b5m apart center-to-center. An oxygen sensor in the form of Pt porphyrin polystyrene beads (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) was deposited into each well and slightly melted to ensure adhesion using previously developed methods [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
